description.plain:
Kimetrius Christopher Foose (born August 4, 1998), better known by his stage name Lil Skies, is an American rapper originally from Chambersburg, PA and raised in Waynesboro, PA.

He is currently signed with All We Got Entertainment through Atlantic Records.

His stage name is derived from his fathers stage name “Dark Skies”, his dad was a huge source of inspiration to him when starting his rap career because, he was also a rapper.

songs.title: Red Roses

description.plain:
“Red Roses” is one of the most popular songs by Pennsylvania-based rapper, Lil Skies. The song features Maryland-based rapper, Landon Cube and has attained millions of listens.

Four months after the initial release of the hit single, Skies and Cube teamed up once again, but this time with the popular video director, Cole Bennett to drop its own music video.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WlosjSe5B8c

The song features upbeat vocals about Skies and Cube’s day-to-day life and their plans for the future, all over a unique production by Menoh Beats.

In an “On The Come Up” video with HotNewHipHop, Lil Skies describes the story of meeting the Chicago producer and first discovering this track’s instrumental as this: he woke up in the middle of the night one time and checked his email for beats (something he didn’t usually do), where he discovered an email from Menoh with the “Red Roses” instrumental attached. Immediately, he enjoyed the vibe that he felt from it and turned it into a complete song with Landon Cube’s assistance.

https://youtu.be/kINFKGy4T4E?t=8m54s

songs.title: Nowadays

description.plain:
Echoing his distaste for a relationship and “fake friends” from his previous hit “Red Roses”, Lil Skies and Landon Cube harmonize over an up-tempo CashMoneyAp production about their fast-paced living and achievements after their newfound fame.

The Cole Bennett-directed music video for the song was released on December 17, 2017.

songs.title: Lust

description.plain:
This is the third single to be dropped prior to Life of a Dark Rose’s full release on January 10th, 2018. The track’s upbeat trap instrumental gives it the perfect party/turn up vibe.

https://www.instagram.com/p/BcnrFtzlXvj/

Skies has explicitly stated in a live show that this is one of, if not his favorite song from the mixtape. While it’s not uncommon, it is notable that he enjoys performing “Lust” multiple times throughout some of his concerts.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yA1ZW3rTlhs
